sentences.english: The groom walks between two rows of guardsmen.
sentences.chinese: “衛兵”們分列兩行，向新郎致意。

sentences.english: The holy trinity is located in the center and is surrounded by apostles and saints.
sentences.chinese: 三位一體位於壁畫中央，十二門徒和諸聖分列四周。

sentences.english: A reading list for the class, divided up by lecture.
sentences.chinese: 課程閱讀資料表依授課單元分列如後。

sentences.english: There are two rows of aspens on either side of the streets.
sentences.chinese: 道路的兩邊分列着整齊的白楊樹。

sentences.english: The Hawks' Al Horford and the Rockets' Luis Scola took 2nd and 3rd spots respectively.
sentences.chinese: 老鷹霍福德和火箭斯科拉分列二三位。

sentences.english: We should adopt the legislation pattern for enterprises that enterprise organization law should be separated from enterprise development law.
sentences.chinese: 我國應將企業組織法和企業發展法分列立法的模式。

sentences.english: Finally you will end up having a lot of words ranging around your starting-point.
sentences.chinese: 最後，以蘋果爲起點，分列出許多詞語而結束。

sentences.english: Sean He and Steve Elmes got second and third place respectively.
sentences.chinese: 何賢磊和史蒂夫分列第二和第三名。
